main event: A civilian witnessed a single unidentified aerial object for 3 seconds in Lawrenceburg, Indiana on August 16, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed at 6:30 PM, with the witness reporting clear skies and a few stars visible.
The object appeared as a still, brighter than the brightest stars, with sharply outlined edges.
The witness reported that the object did not make any sound and did not have any exhaust or vapor trails.
The witness had previously seen a similar object in the same area on August 5, 1966.
The witness was with two other people, Lawrence Rauch and Jane Couch, who also witnessed the object.
